  "id": "PLACE_darksalt_rampart",
  "label": "Darksalt Rampart",
  "description": "Darksalt Rampart rises from Brineshade’s basaltic uplands as a long, wall-like massif of columnar black rock veined with evaporite seams. Wind abrasion and mineral haze polish the exposed faces into alternating matte and glassy bands that flare under Saltharrow’s hard white radiance. High tidal stresses fracture the crest into stepped scarps and tilted plates, leaving broad talus aprons dusted with pale salt. Thin atmospheric currents funnel along the rampart’s length, sustaining persistent low-lying haze that fixes the mountain as a prominent optical landmark across the flats.",
